<MudPaper Elevation="4" class="pa-10 mb-10">
    <MudText Typo="Typo.h5">Design</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" class="mt-5">Mechanical</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
        The mechanical design of WLA drones is carried out with SolidWorks. It contains 2 main components, including the main central structure and the side motor structure.
    </MudText>
    <MudGrid class="pt-5">
        <MudItem xs="12" sm="6">
            <MudCard>
                <MudCardMedia Image="images/WLA/WLA-tube.png" Height="300" />
                <MudCardContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2">Main central structure</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                        The purpose of the main central structure is to provide a waterproof space to store the electronics and battery.
                        It is constructed with an acrylic tube, dome, and cover with two 3-D printed flanges. It is assembled with O-rings to water seal the internal compartment. 
                        The forward transparent dome provides a space to put a camera for real-time monitoring. 
                    </MudText>   
                </MudCardContent>
            </MudCard>
        </MudItem>
        <MudItem xs="12" sm="6">
            <MudCard>
                <MudCardMedia Image="images/WLA/WLA-arm.png" Height="300" />
                <MudCardContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2">Side motor structure</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                        The purpose of the side motor structures is to provide support and connect the servo and motor assembly to the main central structure. 
                        It is a 3D-printed structure providing a mount and bearing support for the brushless motor mount and the servo motor. 
                        At the bottom, there is a mount for an acrylic wheel to allow the drone to move on the road.
                    </MudText>
                </MudCardContent>
            </MudCard>
        </MudItem>
        <MudItem xs="12" sm="6">
            <MudCard>
                <MudCardMedia Image="images/WLA/WLA-motor.png" Height="300" />
                <MudCardContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2">Servo and motor assembly</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                        WLA drone is powered by four servo and brushless DC motor assemblies.
                        The brushless DC motor and mount, assembled to the side motor structure through bearing and shaft, generate thrust with the propeller.
                        The servo motor is connected to the shaft changing the direction of the thrust produced to allow the drone to operate on land, water, and in the air.
                    </MudText>
                </MudCardContent>
            </MudCard>
        </MudItem>
    </MudGrid>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" class="mt-5">Electronic</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
        The electronic system provides the hardware needed to control the drone. STM32H7 Microcontroller (MCU) is used in this project together with serval other sensors.
    </MudText>
    <MudGrid class="pt-5">
        <MudItem xs="12" sm="6">
            <MudCard>
                <MudCardMedia Image="images/WLA/WLA-electronic.JPG" Height="300" />
                <MudCardContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2">Main board assembly</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                        The main board assembly is stored inside the main central structure. An STM32H7 Nucleo development board is mounted to the middle plate with a daughterboard installed on top.
                        Sensors including, IMU, GPS, TFT screen, RC, and ESC are seated on the daughterboard and connected to the development board with wires.
                        A battery is mounted on the other side. 
                    </MudText>   
                </MudCardContent>
            </MudCard>
        </MudItem>
        <MudItem xs="12" sm="6">
            <MudCard>
                <MudCardMedia Image="images/WLA/WLA-pinout.png" Height="300" />
                <MudCardContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2">Microcontroller pinout</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                        The wiring and layout of the connection between sensors, power, and MCU are conducted using the STM32 CubeMX software.
                        Each pin is configured with different embedded interfaces, such as I2C, SPI, PWM, and ADC. The clock speed and communication protocol is set according to the specification of the sensors.
                    </MudText>
                </MudCardContent>
            </MudCard>
        </MudItem>
    </MudGrid>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" class="mt-5">Software</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
        The embedded software, written in C, processes the sensor data and user RC command to compute the required RPM of each motor for smooth movement. The software is available at <MudLink Href="#" Target="https://github.com/kyfrankie/Water-Land-Air-Drone" Typo="Typo.body2" Color="Color.Tertiary">https://github.com/kyfrankie/Water-Land-Air-Drone</MudLink>.
    </MudText>
    <MudGrid class="pt-5">
        <MudItem xs="12" sm="6">
            <MudCard>
                <MudCardMedia Image="images/WLA/WLA-software.png" Height="300" />
                <MudCardContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2">Flight Control software</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                        The embedded flight control software makes use of the STM32 Hardware Abstraction Layer (HAL) library to configure and process data from and to various embedded interfaces.
                        A custom program is written to process data for the IMU, GPS, RC (remote controller) and SD card, and export data to TFT (screen), servos and motors through PWM.
                    </MudText>
                </MudCardContent>
            </MudCard>
        </MudItem>
        <MudItem xs="12" sm="6">
            <MudCard>
                <MudCardMedia Image="images/WLA/WLA-pid.png" Height="300" />
                <MudCardContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2">PID Controller</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                        A custom PID controller has been programmed and tuned for the WLA drone to command the rotational speed of each motor precisely for smooth and accurate movement.
                        The controller continuously calculates the difference between desired and current states and applies a correction based on tuned proportional, integral, and derivative terms to control the RPM of each motor.
                    </MudText>
                </MudCardContent>
            </MudCard>
        </MudItem>
    </MudGrid>
</MudPaper>

